STEP 2D — CONTEXT BUDGET RULES
Append to CLAUDE.md:

## Context Budget Rules
- Never read a file fully if only a specific function is needed — use grep first
- Never dump raw command output into context — use context-mode sandbox tools
- RTK is active as a transparent proxy — never prefix commands manually with rtk
- Before any multi-file operation, run: fallow . to get a structural map first
- Use ctx_batch_execute for any task requiring more than 2 shell commands
- Use ctx_fetch_and_index for any URL research — never raw WebFetch
- If context usage exceeds 40%, run: ctx stats and prune with ctx_purge if needed
- Maximum CLAUDE.md size: 100 lines. If exceeded, summarise and compress before appending
- For any task with 3+ independent subtasks: spawn parallel sub-agents
  Example: explore backend/, src/routes/, src/services/ in parallel using
  separate sub-agents then synthesise findings — never explore sequentially
- Never do sequential file exploration — parallelise across directories
- Use git worktrees for any feature that touches more than 2 modules

