## Agent Harness Rules
- Before any feature work: run /grill-with-docs — no exceptions
- Before any bug fix: run /diagnose — define reproduce steps first
- All new features: use /tdd — write failing test first, then implement
- Every week: run /improve-codebase-architecture — prevent entropy
- If a task has more than 3 steps: write a plan, get confirmation, then execute
- If uncertain about scope: use /zoom-out before touching any file
- Never modify more than one module boundary in a single session
- Hermes handles all background/scheduled tasks — never block the IDE on long-running work
- claude-mem and Hermes serve different time horizons — never duplicate between them
- If Hermes MCP tool routing fails: restart with hermes mcp serve — always the first suspect
- Hooks run at the OS level on every write — do not attempt to bypass them
- RTK is a transparent proxy — never prefix commands manually with rtk
- Run: rtk gain --graph at the end of each week to review token savings
- Sentrux score is the architectural north star — if score drops more than 100
  points in a session: stop, fix the regression, then continue
- Run: sentrux check . at the start and end of every session
- Never let sentrux score trend downward across consecutive sessions
- Browser Harness is DISABLED by default — enable only when a browser automation
  task is explicitly needed (E2E testing, scraping, form automation, UI testing)
- To enable browser-harness: set "disabled": false in settings.json, then run:
  pip install browser-harness and restart Claude Code
- Never use raw Playwright or Selenium when browser-harness is active —
  all browser tasks route through browser-harness only

## Session Start Checklist
1. Read .claude/session-notes.md
